# 🚀 Day 35/90 – Creating the Design System

Welcome to **Day 35!** 🎉

Yesterday, you created the **wireframes** (the blueprint of the app).

Today, we'll create something that every professional app has:

> **A Design System**

A design system is a collection of rules that define how your app looks and feels.

It ensures that every screen has the same style, making the app look professional and trustworthy.

---

# 🎯 Today's Goal

By the end of today, you'll understand:

* How to choose colors
* How to select fonts
* How to design buttons
* How to style cards
* How to choose icons
* How to keep every screen consistent

---

# What is a Design System?

Imagine a hospital.

Every doctor wears a similar uniform.

Every sign uses the same colors.

Every room follows the same style.

This consistency helps people feel comfortable.

Apps work the same way.

If every screen has different colors, fonts, and buttons, users feel confused.

A Design System keeps everything consistent.

---

# Our Brand Personality

Your Blood Report Analyzer should feel:

* ✅ Trustworthy
* ✅ Professional
* ✅ Calm
* ✅ Clean
* ✅ Easy to use

It should **not** feel:

* ❌ Like a game
* ❌ Overly colorful
* ❌ Busy or cluttered

Healthcare apps should reduce anxiety, not create it.

---

# Step 1 – Choose Primary Colors

For healthcare, colors should communicate trust.

### Primary Color

🟦 Blue

Purpose:

* Main buttons
* Header
* Navigation

Blue is widely associated with trust and reliability.

---

### Success Color

🟢 Green

Purpose:

* Normal test results
* Success messages

Example:

```text
Hemoglobin

Normal
```

---

### Warning Color

🟡 Orange

Purpose:

* Borderline values
* Needs Attention

Example:

```text
Vitamin D

Insufficient
```

---

### Alert Color

🔴 Red

Purpose:

* Critical values
* Errors

Example:

```text
HbA1c

High
```

---

### Neutral Colors

⚪ White

Background

⚫ Dark Gray

Text

Light Gray

Cards and dividers

These colors make the app easier to read.

---

# Step 2 – Typography

Use one clean font throughout the app.

Recommended:

* Roboto (Android)
* Inter
* SF Pro (iPhone)

For Flutter, **Roboto** is a great default.

---

# Font Sizes

| Element         | Size |
| --------------- | ---- |
| App Title       | 28   |
| Screen Title    | 22   |
| Section Heading | 18   |
| Normal Text     | 16   |
| Small Text      | 14   |

Avoid fonts smaller than 14 for important content.

---

# Step 3 – Buttons

Every button should have a consistent style.

### Primary Button

```text
------------------------

Upload Report

------------------------
```

Use for the main action.

---

### Secondary Button

```text
History
```

Use for less important actions.

---

# Button Rules

Buttons should:

* Have rounded corners
* Be large enough to tap easily
* Have consistent spacing
* Use the same style across the app

---

# Step 4 – Cards

Cards help organize information.

Example:

```text
------------------------

Hemoglobin

13.2

Normal

------------------------
```

Each blood test result should be shown inside its own card.

---

# Step 5 – Icons

Use simple, universally recognized icons.

| Feature    | Suggested Icon |
| ---------- | -------------- |
| Upload     | 📤             |
| History    | 📄             |
| Compare    | 📊             |
| Profile    | 👤             |
| AI Summary | 🤖             |
| Search     | 🔍             |
| Settings   | ⚙️             |

Avoid decorative icons that don't add meaning.

---

# Step 6 – Spacing

Good spacing makes the app feel less crowded.

Example:

❌ Bad

```text
NameAgeBloodGroup
```

✅ Good

```text
Name

Age

Blood Group
```

Leave enough space between sections.

---

# Step 7 – Result Cards

Every blood test should look the same.

Example:

```text
--------------------------------

Hemoglobin

13.2 g/dL

🟢 Normal

--------------------------------
```

Another example:

```text
--------------------------------

Vitamin D

18 ng/mL

🟡 Insufficient

--------------------------------
```

Consistent formatting helps users compare results quickly.

---

# Step 8 – AI Summary Box

This should stand out from the test results.

Example:

```text
--------------------------------

AI Summary

Your report shows that most values
are within the reference ranges.
Vitamin D is below the reference
range shown on the report.
Discuss these findings with your
doctor if you have concerns.

--------------------------------
```

Keep the language simple and supportive.

---

# Step 9 – Navigation Bar

Bottom navigation is familiar to most users.

```text
--------------------------------

🏠 Home

📄 History

📊 Compare

👤 Profile

--------------------------------
```

Use the same navigation on every main screen.

---

# Step 10 – Loading Screen

When AI is analyzing the report:

```text
--------------------------------

Analyzing Report...

Please wait.

⏳

--------------------------------
```

Users should always know that work is in progress.

---

# Accessibility

Remember that many users may be older adults.

Design with:

* Large text
* High contrast
* Big buttons
* Clear labels
* Minimal typing

This makes the app usable for a wider audience.

---

# Design Principles for Our App

Our app should always be:

* Simple
* Consistent
* Readable
* Trustworthy
* Fast
* Calm

If a design choice doesn't support these goals, reconsider it.

