# 👨‍🏫 Mentor's Note

Today you created the **visual identity** of your app.

Many new founders focus only on features. But users often judge quality within the first few seconds of opening an app. A consistent design builds confidence before they even upload their first report.

For your Blood Report Analyzer, I would add one more rule to the design system:

> **Every health status should include both a color and text.**

For example:

* 🟢 **Normal**
* 🟡 **Needs Attention**
* 🔴 **Consult a Doctor**

This makes the app easier to understand for users with color vision deficiencies and ensures the meaning is always clear.

**Tomorrow (Day 36)** we'll define the **Brand Identity** of your app:

* App name
* Logo concept
* Tagline
* Mission
* Vision
* Brand values

These elements will make your Blood Report Analyzer feel like a real healthcare product rather than just a software project.
